Akbank Hires Banks for One-Year Loan in Euros, Dollars

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-08-12T13:43:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/akbank-hires-banks-for-one-year-loan-in-euros-dollars-1-.html
Akbank TAS (AKBNK) , the Turkish bank part-
owned by Citigroup Inc., hired a group of international banks to
get a syndicated loan with 693.5 million euros and $374.5
million tranches.  The loan will have a maturity of one-year, Akbank said in a
statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  today. The loan will be
signed with banks on Aug. 17, the bank said in an e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Bentley at 
 mbentley3@bloomberg.net  